curam.util.xmlserver

Interface DocumentGenerator


  • public interface DocumentGenerator
    This interface is to be implemented by all DocumentGenerators that are going to be registered with XMLServer for the purpose of printing documents.

    • Method Detail

      • generateDocument

        void generateDocument(javax.xml.transform.Transformer xslTemplate,
                      java.io.InputStreamReader xmlDataStream,
                      java.io.OutputStream docOutput)
               throws XMLJobException
        This method should be implemented to generate the document for a job type. The method is provided with the xml template and xml data to be merged to create the document. The document result should be sent to the output stream provided.
        Parameters:
        xslTemplate - The XSL template transformer.
        xmlDataStream - The input stream from which to read the XML data.
        docOutput - The output stream for the generated document.
        Throws:
        XMLJobException - Generic exception to be thrown on error. Exception handing should be handled within the implemented method.

      • getFileExtension

        java.lang.String getFileExtension()
        This method should return a String containing the file extension for the file to be generated. For example if generating a HTML file the method should return the String ".html".
        Returns:
        The extension of the file to be generated.
